medications","It primarily affects the hip bursa","It is usually associated with systemic symptoms like fever"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBursitis is the inflammation of a bursa, which is a small fluid-filled sac that reduces friction between tissues of the body. Infective bursitis occurs when a bursa becomes infected, often by bacteria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInfective bursitis is most commonly caused by bacterial infections, particularly by \u003Cstrong\u003Edirect trauma or inoculation\u003C/strong\u003E into the bursa. This can occur through cuts, abrasions, or puncture wounds that introduce bacteria, such as \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/em\u003E, into the bursa.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is most commonly caused by viral infections\u003C/strong\u003E - Bacterial infections are the primary cause\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is usually associated with systemic symptoms like fever\u003C/strong\u003E - While fever can occur, local symptoms are more common\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt primarily affects the hip bursa\u003C/strong\u003E - The olecranon and prepatellar bursae are more commonly affected\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is best treated with antiviral medications\u003C/strong\u003E - Antibiotics are the appropriate treatment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInfective bursitis often presents with localised pain, swelling, and redness over the affected bursa, and it requires prompt medical treatment to prevent complications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Infective bursitis is often caused by bacterial infection, commonly due to skin flora such as Staphylococcus aureus.","The infection 